         VERSION=0.9.4
       BUILD_API=2
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tgz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
        WEB_SITE=http://www.ph-home.de/opensource/kde3/kwlaninfo
   SOURCE_URL[0]=$WEB_SITE/$SOURCE
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
          MD5[0]='65d78e814d0ad388f6ebd3e1d2f367a3'
         ENTERED=20040112
         UPDATED=20040720
SHORT="KDE applet to monitor wlan interfaces"
cat << EOF
KWireless provides some information about wlan interfaces using
/proc/net/wireless. It's a kicker panel applet and so you must start it with a
right click on a empty space in the kicker panel and then add it using
"add->applet->kwireless".

At the moment it only works properly if the wlan interface is set to "managed"
mode (access point).  
EOF
